Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Spread oil in the bottom of a 9 inch square baking dish. Sift flour into a medium bowl, then beat in eggs. Gradually stir in milk, water, salt and pepper. Beat well. Place sausages in baking dish and pour batter mixture over all. Bake in the preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden and risen.